# Home

neat rows of accordion folders = 整齐几排文件夹
only half lying = 半真半假地说
take attendance = 点名
do the seating chart = 排座位表
They were okay. = 他们还行吧（含糊、不想评价）
went out of his way to tell me = 特意去告诉我
what sweet kids they are = 他们是多么乖的孩子（感叹句结构）
I kept looking at Daisy. = 我一直看着Daisy（keep doing 表持续）
rubbing her ear = 给她揉耳朵
flea-scratch shake = 挠痒后那种抖动（狗的动作）
he was the least nice = 他是最不友好的
maybe I'm getting them confused = 也许我把他们搞混了
brushed forward = （头发）往前梳
the kind of kid who's one way in front of grown-ups and another way in front of kids = 在大人面前一套，在孩子面前一套
Yeah, I guess. = 嗯，大概吧（不确定语气）
hate those = 讨厌那种人（those 指那类人）
What's the deal with your face? = 你脸怎么回事？（不礼貌表达）
Were you in a fire or something? = 你是被火烧过吗之类的？（or something 随口补充）
she was completely shocked = 她完全震惊了
He didn't say it in a mean way. = 他不是恶意地说的
He was just asking. = 他只是问问而已
admit that = 承认……（正式但常用）
so nervous that = 紧张到……（so…that 结果结构）
butterflies in my stomach = 心里发慌、紧张（习语）
more like pigeons flying around my insides = 夸张表达“非常紧张”
acted all excited = 表现得特别兴奋（all 加强语气）
reversed sides = 立场对调
whether I should go or not = 我该不该去（whether 引导选择）
proud of how I'd handled myself = 为我的应对方式感到骄傲
turning into quite the strong man = 正在变成一个真正坚强的人（quite the 强调）
had been right all along = 一直以来都是对的
wasn't so sure anymore = 不再那么确定了（比 not sure 更自然）
seemed relieved = 看起来松了一口气
just a few blocks from = 离……只有几个街区
try to avoid = 尽量避免
roaming around = 到处闲逛
every brick and every tree trunk and every crack = 排比强调“非常熟悉”
a street I've been down a million times = 走过无数次的街（夸张表达）
looked totally different = 看起来完全不同
pushing strollers = 推着婴儿车
kind of no-nonsense = 有点干脆利落、不废话
shoot someone a look = 向某人投去一个眼神
resisted doing something = 忍住没做某事
specifically told us not to = 特别叮嘱我们不要
cursing under his breath = 小声咒骂
scrunched up his face = 皱起脸
tapping his forehead = 敲着额头（表示在思考）
tiny braid = 小辫子
slide under the desk = 钻到桌子下面（逃避的心理画面）
at recess = 在课间
becomes totally deformed = 完全变形
shriveled up = 皱缩
peeked at = 偷偷看了一眼
a lot of shuffling around = 一阵乱动、收拾书包的声音
doodling in my notebook = 在本子上乱画
every once in a while = 偶尔
called out = 大声说出
ground rule = 基本规则
plaque next to the door = 门旁的牌匾
sloppy handwriting = 潦草的字
spread all the way across = 横跨整个

Basically, a precept is anything that helps guide us when making decisions about really important things. Like a motto. Like a famous quote.像座右铭，像名言（类比解释法）
I resisted spinning the combination even though everyone else was doing it. 尽管别人都在转密码锁，我还是忍住没转（resist + doing）
She had only hesitated for a millionth of a second, but I could tell the moment she saw me. 她只犹豫了极短一瞬间，但我能感觉到她看到我的那一刻（细微情绪捕捉）
I was so nervous that the butterflies in my stomach were more like pigeons flying around my insides. = 我紧张得肚子里的蝴蝶都像鸽子一样乱飞（情绪具象化写法）
Up until a few days before, we still weren't sure I would be going to school at all. = 直到几天前，我们还不确定我要不要去上学（时间铺垫）
Mom and Dad had reversed sides on whether I should go or not. = 爸妈在我该不该去这件事上立场对调了
Dad had told me he was really proud of how I'd handled myself. = 爸爸说他为我处理事情的方式感到骄傲
I could tell she wasn't so sure anymore. = 我能看出来她不再那么确定了（心理观察表达）
Mom seemed relieved that we would all be going together. = 妈妈似乎因为我们一起去而松了口气
In general, I try to avoid blocks where there are lots of kids roaming around. = 一般来说我会避开有很多孩子闲逛的街区
Everybody knows me and I know everybody. = 大家都认识我，我也认识大家（强调熟悉感）
I know every brick and every tree trunk and every crack in the sidewalk. = 我熟悉到连每块砖和每条裂缝都知道（排比强化）
I love my neighborhood, which is why it was so strange to be walking down these blocks feeling like it was all new to me. = 我爱我的社区，所以当我走在这些街上却觉得一切陌生时才会那么奇怪（which is why 解释原因）
A street I've been down a million times looked totally different for some reason. = 一条我走过无数次的街不知为何看起来完全不同（熟悉感崩塌）
When I call your name, come up and I'll hand you a folder with your name on it.当我叫到你的名字，上来拿属于你的文件夹（课堂常用结构）
Be forewarned that you cannot switch lockers and you can't switch locks.提前告诉你们不能换储物柜（forewarned 更正式表达）
As she went down the list, I noticed that the seat next to me was the only one still empty.当她往下念名单时，我注意到我旁边的座位是唯一空着的（as 表示同时发生）
Although I didn't look at him directly, I could tell he did not want to move next to me.虽然我没直接看他，但我能感觉到他不想坐我旁边（although + 心理判断）
I could tell just by the way he dragged his backpack on the floor.我从他拖书包的方式就能看出来（just by the way… 观察细节）
He plopped his backpack up really high so it was kind of like a wall between his desk and mine.他把书包放得很高，像在我们之间筑了一道墙（行为象征心理距离）
